================ TOKENIZATION ================

15. tokens = word_tokenize(text)
Splits sentence into individual words.

Output Example:
['Text', 'analytics', 'is', 'the', 'process', ...]

Each word is called a token.

Purpose:
Break sentence into smaller units.



================ POS TAGGING ================

16. pos = pos_tag(tokens)
Assigns grammatical tags to words.

Example:
Text       -> NN
analytics  -> NNS
is         -> VBZ

17. Common POS Tags

NN  -> Noun
NNS -> Plural Noun
VB  -> Verb
VBD -> Verb Past Tense
VBZ -> Verb Present
JJ  -> Adjective
DT  -> Determiner

Example:
the -> DT

18. print(f"{word:<15} -> {tag}")

<15:
Allocates 15 character spaces for alignment.

Example:
Text            -> NN
analytics       -> NNS

Purpose:
Makes output properly formatted.



================ STOPWORD REMOVAL ================

19. stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
Loads English stopwords.

20. filtered = [word for word in tokens if word.lower() not in stop_words]
Removes stopwords from tokens.

Purpose:
Keep meaningful words only.

Before:
Text analytics is the process of analyzing text data

After:
['Text', 'analytics', 'process', 'analyzing', 'text', 'data', ...]



================ STEMMING ================

